<main id="main-content">
<!-- HERO -->
<header class="page-hero">
  <div class="hero-eyebrow">Who's Standing With Cortney</div>
  <h1>Endorsed by<br>Working People</h1>
  <p>Nurses, teachers, union members, faith leaders, and neighbors across OH-11 who know this district deserves a real representative — not a party placeholder.</p>
</header>

<!-- INDIVIDUAL ENDORSEMENTS -->
<section class="section" aria-labelledby="individual-heading">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="reveal">
      <p class="category-label">Individual Endorsements</p>
      <h2 class="section-heading" id="individual-heading">Voices from the District</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">Real people. Real stakes. These aren't politicians — they're your neighbors.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- ADD INDIVIDUAL ENDORSEMENTS HERE as they come in. Template:
    <article class="endorsement-card reveal">
      <div class="endorser-name">First Name L.</div>
      <div class="endorser-title">Title / Occupation, City</div>
      <p class="endorser-quote">Their quote in their own words.</p>
    </article>
    -->

    <div class="endorsement-grid">

      <article class="endorsement-card reveal">
        <p class="endorser-name">Patrick McGuire</p>
        <p class="endorser-title">McGuire Digital Design &amp; Development, Lead Sign Tech Image360 South Tampa — Jefferson County Born Native</p>
        <p class="endorser-quote">I'm not a voter in Ohio's 11th, I'm states away now... but Ohio is my home state, and when a woman from Ohio says she's going to fight, you better believe it's going to be a slobberknocker. I've worked with Cortney for only a short time, but that's all it takes to see who she is: a woman who knows exactly what she stands for, says it plainly, and doesn't back down. She's brave in a way that most people only talk about. It takes real courage to stand up and stand out.. especially when you're fighting for the marginalized, the overlooked, and the working people who've been ignored for too long. She's not doing this for a career. She's doing this because somebody has to... and she decided it was going to be her.</p>
      </article>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<hr class="section-divider">

<!-- ORGANIZATIONAL ENDORSEMENTS -->
<section class="section" aria-labelledby="org-heading">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="reveal">
      <p class="category-label">Organizational Endorsements</p>
      <h2 class="section-heading" id="org-heading">Organizations Standing With Us</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">Community groups, local organizations, and advocacy coalitions who believe OH-11 deserves real representation.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="org-grid">
      <div class="org-card org-featured reveal">
        <picture>
          <source srcset="assets/images/CI-CC-1080x1080-Peterson-OH11.webp" type="image/webp">
          <img src="assets/images/CI-CC-1080x1080-Peterson-OH11.jpeg" alt="Cortney Peterson — Courage Candidate, Citizens' Impeachment — Courage for Democracy" class="org-featured-img" width="1080" height="1080" loading="lazy">
        </picture>
        <div class="org-featured-body">
          <div class="org-name" style="font-size:1.2rem;margin-bottom:0.4rem"><a href="https://couragefordemocracy.com/candidate/cortney-peterson/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color:inherit;text-decoration:none;border-bottom:1.5px solid var(--coral)">Citizens' Impeachment — Courage for Democracy</a></div>
          <div class="org-type" style="margin-bottom:1rem">Democracy &amp; Anti-Corruption — Courage Candidate</div>
          <p style="font-size:0.95rem;color:var(--text-light);line-height:1.7">Cortney Peterson has been recognized as a <strong style="color:var(--plum)">Courage Candidate</strong> by Citizens' Impeachment — Courage for Democracy for her commitment to anti-corruption, accountability, and putting democracy back in the hands of working people.</p>
          <a href="https://couragefordemocracy.com/candidate/cortney-peterson/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.4rem;margin-top:1rem;font-weight:700;font-size:0.85rem;color:var(--plum);text-decoration:none;letter-spacing:0.04em;text-transform:uppercase">View Full Profile →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- ADD MORE ORG CARDS HERE as endorsements come in:
      <div class="org-card reveal">
        <div class="org-icon" aria-hidden="true">EMOJI</div>
        <div>
          <div class="org-name">Organization Name</div>
          <div class="org-type">Type</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      -->
    </div>

    <p style="margin-top:2rem;font-size:0.9rem;color:var(--text-light);font-style:italic">* Organizational endorsements reflect the views of each organization's leadership and not necessarily all members. More announcements coming soon.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ENDORSE CORTNEY CTA -->
<section class="endorse-cta" aria-labelledby="endorse-heading">
  <div class="endorse-cta-inner">
  <div class="endorse-cta-text">
  <h2 id="endorse-heading">Add Your Name</h2>
  <p>Are you an individual, community leader, or organization that wants to publicly support Cortney? Let us know — your name helps other voters know they're not alone.</p>
  <blockquote class="endorse-pull">
    "When a nurse from Ashtabula says she's going to fight for you — believe her. This is the most grassroots, genuine campaign I've been part of in thirty years."
    <cite>— Retired union organizer, Cuyahoga County</cite>
  </blockquote>
  </div>

  <div class="endorse-form-wrap">
    <div id="endorseSuccess" class="endorse-success" role="alert">
      <div class="check" aria-hidden="true">✅</div>
      <h3>Thank you for your support!</h3>
      <p>We'll reach out to confirm your endorsement. Your name matters — and it helps other voters know they're not alone.</p>
    </div>
    <form id="endorseForm" name="endorsement" method="POST" action="/success.html" data-netlify="true" netlify-honeypot="bot-field">
      <input type="hidden" name="form-name" value="endorsement">
      <p hidden><label>Don't fill this out: <input name="bot-field"></label></p>
      <div class="form-row">
        <div class="form-group">
          <label for="firstName">First Name</label>
          <input type="text" id="firstName" name="firstName" placeholder="First" required autocomplete="given-name">
        </div>
        <div class="form-group">
          <label for="lastName">Last Name</label>
          <input type="text" id="lastName" name="lastName" placeholder="Last" required autocomplete="family-name">
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="form-group">
        <label for="email">Email Address</label>
        <input type="email" id="email" name="email" placeholder="you@example.com" required autocomplete="email">
      </div>
      <div class="form-group">
        <label for="city">City / Neighborhood</label>
        <input type="text" id="city" name="city" placeholder="e.g. Cleveland Heights" autocomplete="address-level2">
      </div>
      <div class="form-group">
        <label for="endorserType">I am endorsing as a...</label>
        <select id="endorserType" name="endorserType" required>
          <option value="" disabled selected>Select one</option>
          <option value="individual">Individual / Voter</option>
          <option value="organization">Organization or Group</option>
          <option value="faith">Faith Leader</option>
          <option value="labor">Union / Labor Leader</option>
          <option value="elected">Current or Former Elected Official</option>
          <option value="other">Other</option>
        </select>
      </div>
      <div class="form-group">
        <label for="statement">Your Endorsement Statement (optional)</label>
        <textarea id="statement" name="statement" placeholder="Why are you supporting Cortney? We may quote this on the site with your permission."></textarea>
      </div>
      <button type="submit" class="btn-submit">Submit Endorsement</button>
    </form>
  </div><!-- end endorse-form-wrap -->
  </div><!-- end endorse-cta-inner -->
</section>

</main>